Description: Fragment of oal handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay near fine buff; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 51, 3. Name Onasimos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0395.31.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1717)
